inn1.comm: full in length, well outside off and Gambhir gets across to drive to covers
short of length, moving from middle towards off, Gambhir lets it come to him before defending it to the off side
And here we go, the first boundary of the game. Full, outside off and Gambhir square drives past the backward point fielder.
sharp lifting delivery. Super stuff. It kicked up towards the head and Gambhir just about yanked his face off the line.

Dropped by Younis Khan at second slip. Another delivery that reared up from short of length, shoulder high and moving away from Gambhir who fended it off with an open face and it flew to the left of Younis who lunged but ended up paliming it over his shoulder.
now then ... that one really shot through low. A surra! It cut in from just outside off and kept low, Sehwag crouched but couldn't put bat to ball and it went just past the off stump
hint of inswing. Full and drifting towards pads and Gambhir flicks it away for a single down to fine leg
full and angling away from Sehwag, left alone
Another one angling away and again Sehwag doesn't offer any stroke
nagging line and length, slanting across Sehwag who thrusts his front leg across, covers the off stump, and shoulders arms
tries to get this one to swing back in to the right-handed Sehwag, it does swing but goes down the leg side and Akmal couldn't get across in time
gets it back to the outside-off line, left alone
good delivery. He got it to curve in slightly from just outside off and Sehwag square drives to the off side
full in length, outside off stump, dabbed to third man for a single
beaten outside off stump. Cutting away from Gambhir who tries to run it down to third man
Another cutting away, this time from short of length and Gambhir hangs his bat out, opens the bat-face and runs it past the slip fielder.
another one slanting away, left alone
fullish, on the off and middle, Gambhir leans forward to work it to midwicket
pushed to left of mid-on for  a single
Sehwag breaks free with a whip through midwicket. It was full and on the leg stump line, he allowed it to come to him before wristing it through the on side
gets back to get in line of a delivery moving towards the middle stump and defends to the off side.
slightly open stance to the left-armer and pushes a length delivery on the off stump to cover point for a quick single. Gambhir and Sehwag get across to have a chat.

mis fielded by Salman Butt. It was pushed gently to him at backward point, he ran in and failed to pick it up and the ball rolled past him and they will get a single. The fielding hasn't been good so far but it's early days still.
high harmless bouncer down the leg side
stays beside the line of the delivery on the middle and off, opens the bat-face and runs it to third man
nice timing from Sehwag and again Salman Butt makes a mess. sehwag went back to caress a length delivery past point and Butt chased, tried a sliding dive, made a mess and gave away an extra run
again pushed to Salman at backward point who stops it.
on the middle and leg, clipped to square leg
He leaned across to unfurl a square drive to a fullish delivery outside off stump. Easy on the eye.
slashed to third man boundary. A touch short in length, outside off stump, Sehwag rocks back and chops it down to the boundary
Three in a row. This time from Gambhir. He got across to a full length delivery well outside off stump and knifed it through covers. Gambhir is  standing well outside the crease.
moves into the line of a length delivery outside off and he wants to drive on the up but ends up mistiming it to the off side. Sehwag gets across to have a chat
waits for the length delivery to come to him before tapping it gently close on the off side and they get a single.
angling away from Sehwag, who has played very carefully today, gets behind the line to push it to backward point.
on the middle and Sehwag, who is standing inside the crease, defends to the off side
similar delivery and again Sehwag pats it to the off side.
Short and outside off, cut to third man
on the middle and leg, worked to square leg
walks into the line and steers the length delivery to backward point
outside the off stump, dabbed to the point region
ah! charge and a miss. Gambhir ran down the wicket, Wahab hurled it short, Gambhir tried to cut it but missed
No mistake this time. He waits at his stance and Wahab offers another short-pitched delivery outside off which he cuts to the point boundary. he hopped in the air to get on top of the bounce
slanting across Sehwag who pushes it to left of short cover
goes back to create length and opens the bat-face to steer a length delivery on off and middle to third man
leans forward to push a full length delivery towards mid-off for a quick single
on a length, angling away, cut to wide third man. He wanted to give himself some room to create width but didn't get much room as he desired
short-pitched delivery outside off stump and Gambhir cuts over point for couple of runs
beaten outside off. Fuller in length and Gambhir decides late to dab it to third man and can't connect
short of length, just outside off stump and Sehwag gets right behind the line and defends solidly.
short of length and down the leg side and that's easy pickings for Sehwag who waits for the ball to come to him before lapping it around the corner to fine leg.
from round the stumps, coming in towards the off stump and is guided to third man for a single.
steered to point region
just outside off stump, cut to backward point

Dropped  by Younis standing at wide slip. Gambhir had tried to slash a length delivery on the up and it flew to Younis' left - quite similar to the earlier drop by him - and he clanged it again. The fielding today has been pretty poor.
on the pads and that's creamed away behind square, good wrists there and makes the most of the errant line
full and outside off, Sehwag lines up a big one over the infield but is done in by the pace, pushed to cover
cramps him for room but he's  waited till the last moment and glided that towards third man
in-dipper from over the wicket, starts just outside off and comes in, big inside edge that deflects onto the pads, massive appeal but that was never going to be given
rapped on the pads again, better line this and some good cut into the left-hander, they sneak a legbye towards short third man
that's streaky but he ensured he played it late, angling in from round the wicket, Sehwag backs away and steers it fine, past the keeper for four, no chance for the keeper
slightly outside off, too close to cut, thick bottom edge prevents him from getting his timing, dribbles to cover
good-length ball again, pats to the off side and takes off for a quick one
more tip-and-run tactics, drops it close to him behind square and they take off, Salman Butt tries for the direct hit but that misses, he might have made it anyway
short of a length, angling into the right hander, glided to third man and they're away, take the first one quickly and hurry back for the second
slightly wide of the stumps, tapped away effortlessly to third man, sensible from the batsmen

slapped towards cover and they think of a single, but Sehwag is quickly sent back, Malik swoops down and sends in a direct hit towards the bowler's end, strikes Sehwag on the hand as the ball deflects, seems to be in some pain
driven crisply but straight to cover, four in the ring there
good-length ball, angling in towards off, tapped towards third man for a single
leans forward to push to right of Malik at mid-off who doesn't make a clean stop. Hmm...

full, from round the stumps, just outside off and Sehwag drives on the up and over the bowler's head. The bat-handle rotated a touch and timing was not perfect but there was still enough meat to go the boundary
in the zone outside off and left alone
charges out to a length delivery, stays outside leg to be adjacent to the line of a delivery on middle and drives but straight to short cover
slower off cutter on the middle, Gambhir waits, shuffles across to dab it behind square leg
on a length, on the middle and leg, wristed to long leg for a single
again he comes down the track but mistimes a drive to the leg side as the bat-handle rotates in his hands

Controversy there. Finally they take a catch or do they  Hold on .. Akmal has grounded it. It was a length delivery that straightened with a bit of bounce outside off, a shufling Sehwag jabbed at it and it went to right of Akmal who lunged and it bobbed up off the gloves and as he tried to pick it up it looked as if it hit the ground. Akmal had his back to the stumps as he had twisted his body to get it. Sehwag had a look, saw him celebrating and walked back to the pavilion. some one from the dressing room asked him to stop. And now he is walking back to the middle. the umpires are on the walkie talkie and the Pakistan players are having drinks. Malik is talking to the umpires, Sehwag is still there in the middle. What  drama. It did touch the ground no doubt. NOT OUT is the verdict
leans forward to place it to right of mid-on for a single
Shot boss! Fullish, on the middle and Sehwag drilled it straight along the ground and past the bowler. Clean smooth downswing of the bat
allows the ball to come into him before turning it past the square leg
full and outside off stump, guided to backward point
cutting away from Gambhir, nothing alarming, just a bit and its run down to third man
full and outside off stump, Sehwag is well inside the crease, he is late in leaning forward but opens the bat-face and steers it very well through the vacant slip region and that's his fifty.
short-pitched delivery, down the leg side, Sehwag stands on his toes and laps it around the corner to the fine-leg boundary
short and wide down the leg side.
dabbed to point region
outside off, a flirt and a miss. Just past the outside edge.
lifting delivery from a length around off and middle and that extra bounce surprised Sehwag and he was beaten, trying to punch it to point
on the middle, straightens and Sehwag gets a leading edge to covers, trying to turn it to the leg side
short of length, on the off and middle, keeps a tad low and Gambhir crouches, taps it close on the off side, one look at each other and off they rush across for another smart quick single

just over Afridi at point. Another leading edge as Sehwag tries to work a length delivery on middle and off to the leg side and it went in the air, Afridi was late in reacting as it happens with leading edges, ran back but couldn't reach. George reckons. AB de Villiers would have caught it.
short and wide, cut to deep point
leans forward to defend a full length delivery to cover point for a single
beaten outside off. Another instance where Sehwag hang his bat out in an effort to run it through the vacant slip region
beaten again. This time he was not trying to dab it to third man but was beaten by a nice little leg cutter
And again. deja-vu. He was late in leaning forward and was searching for that delivery outside off stump

Three good deliveries wasted by a poor one- short and well outside off. Sehwag gets his back leg across to outside-off and cuts it hard to the point boundary. Gul kicked the ground in frustration after Sehwag hammered it.
on a length, just outside off stump,, Gambhir waits for the ball to come to him, taps it close on the off side and rushes across for a single and there is a overthrow at the striker's end
Charges down the track, towards leg side and heaves a length delivery over wide mid-on
on the middle, full in length, moving towards middle and leg, Gambhir calmly nudges it behind square leg for a single
outside the off stump, moving away, Sehwag is on the back foot dabbing it to the third-man region
gets forward to the line and drives on the up to mid-off
full and outside off stump, slashes to third man

tad short in length, outside off stump, cut to third man for another single. The pitch has been a slightly sluggish and so they have tried not to hit too many deliveries on the up, have waited for the ball to come and have nudged many to third man and behind square
again he goes back, opens the bat-face and runs it behind square on the off side
banged in short and Gambhir drops his wrists, gets the bat out of the line and sways away
fuller and on driven to wide mid-on for a single and that's his eight odi fifty, second against Pakistan. He has run well, taken calculated risks now and then and was dropped twice by Younis.
legcutter outside off and again Sehwag is beaten, pushing his bat inside the line. Gul has troubled him with that legcutter on a few occasions.
There you go again. Again a touch late in coming forward to defend and the ball cuts past the outside edge
walks down the track and works a length delivery to square leg
Sehwag goes for the big hit to long-on. He cleared the front leg and went through the line but got more elevation then necessary and it dropped inside the ropes and came to a halt.
on the middle and leg, turned past square leg
Slapped to cover boundary. He moved outside leg stump, Rao pitched it short and Gambhir flat-batted a cut through covers
another charge down the track, Rao hurls it full and well outside off, Gambhir reaches out to run it off the toe end of the bat to third man
goes right back and across and turns a delivery from the off stump to square leg
outside off stump, left alone
outside the off stump and this time Sehwag manages to get it down to third man
comes down the track and slashes to left of sweeper cover
fuller, closer to the off stump and driven to deep cover
length delivery that straightens on the off stump, Sehwag gets behind the line to push it to covers
length delivery that straightens on the off stump, Sehwag gets behind the line to push it to covers
sliding away from Gambhir who rocked back to late cut it through backward point. Nice looking stroke
on the middle and leg, slight turn, pushed to the off side, Sehwag wants a single and Gambhir wisely sends him back
turned past midwicket for a single
threatens to come down the track before going back to cut and Misbah makes a good diving stop
well outside off, Gambhir tries to cut but can't connect
leans forward to push a full delivery back to the bowler
from round the stumps and it's wide outside off stump
First Six of the game. He cleared his front foot and swung a full delivery over long-on. No IPL commentators to shout out that its **** moment of success or it's a *** maximum.
turned past midwicket for a single
And they have broken through. Finally. Gambhir is gone. Full in length, just shaping outside off stump and he tried to run it down to third man but sent it off the face of the bat to Akmal.
short of length, outside off stump and Yuvraj punches it to deep cover
short of length, slanting away from Sehwag who tries to work it to the leg side and edges it to the off side. Free hit coming up and it will be Yuvraj who will face
And it's a wide. So the next ball will be a free hit. Yuvraj was taking an off-stump guard and it was a wide full toss down leg

really full in length, just outside off stump, Yuvraj swings his bat at it and gets an inside edge on to his ankle. Ouch he is in pain and limps across. Sid V, writing the bulletin, drawls, "that was a free hit to his ankle"
on a length, around off stump, cut to third man
leans forward to tap a full delivery to point
slow through the air, turns from leg to middle, defended off the front foot
quicker but shorter and Sehwag rocks back to pull it to deep midwicket boundary
turns it  past midwicket
topspinner outside off stump and Yuvrak opens the bat face to squeeze it through vacant slip region
the ball stopped on Yuvraj and he got a leading edge but the ball doesn't carry to the bowler
short-pitched delivery on the leg stump, Sehwag moves towards middle to evade that
another short one and again down leg, Sehwag laps it to fine leg
well outside off stump and Sehwag has a flash and a miss.

Cramped for room and he is gone! It came in off a length, towards middle and off, from round the stumps angle and Sehwag tried to stay adjacent to the line and cut it to third man but the extra bounce meant he can only edge it to Akmal. It was a leg spinning slower one that broke back in sharply with bounce!
beaten off his first delivery in ODIs. He tried to defend a length delivery outside off and pushed the bat inside the line
above waist-high full toss well outside off and it bounced awkwardly in front of Akmal who didn't collect cleanly
fuller, coming in and pushed to the off side
goes back to jab a full delivery towards midoff. Yusuf wants a single and just about comes back to the crease
driven to long-on
goes back to tap a slider to square leg
on the leg and middle, paddled to the leg side
fuller, on the middle , another leading edge for Yuvraj. He is playing a tad early and too much across the line on a sluggish track like this.
the quicker fuller, almost a yorker, jabbed to the on side
wide down the leg side and Akmal makes an acrobatic stop
stands tall to punch a short of length delivery to covers
short of length one, stops a touch and again, Yuvraj is early into his punch drive and mistimes it
yet another wide down leg.
on a length, on the off stump now and that high back lift comes down to jab it to the off side
full and on the middle, pushed to short and straight midwicket
just outside off stump and pushed through cover point for a single
fullish, just outside off stump, square driven to point where Butt makes a neat stop
tucked towards short midwicket
slightly slower through the air, cracked towards long-on
tossed up on the pads, tries to sweep but that's drifting away, wide called and rightly so
on the pads again, worked away towards the leg side for a quick single
low full toss, driven to long-on for a single, too easy as of now, the run-rate is more than seven and Pakistan are applying no pressure
too far down the leg side again, no need to touch that
too short and that's a meaty hit, rocks back and pulls it away over midwicket, that's a flat six
worked away to mid-off
pushed to cover and they take off, both these can really hurry between the stumps
back-foot punch to the covers, carefully done
back of a length, on middle, pushed towards mid-on
defended to the off side, Yusif is facing his Rajasthan Royals' team-mate Tanvir
watchful front-foot defense, pitched on leg and strikes his pad, big appeal from the bowler but that's not given, probably missing off
and another big appeal, this time it looked closer, but not given again, that might have been closer
drilled through midwicket, easy single there

he's holed out, he tossed that up there, Yusuf stood tall and tried to whack that over long-off but he's struck that straight to Rao, hardly got his timing right through this brief stay, 12-ball 3 for Yusuf on debut, Afridi strikes
pushed to mid-on
driven to mid-off this time, Afridi keeping it quiet here
defended to the off side
quicker one this time, big appeal for lbw but that was probably missing off, not given
leans forward to push a full delivery to covers
that high back lift and he is pushing too early and the ball rolls over to the off side
jabbed to the off side.
leans forward to drive a full pitched delivery to long-on
full in length, worked to the on side
leans forward to defend to the off side now
leans forward to push close on the off side for a single and he is off the mark
full one and is driven to long-on
slow through the air, full, on the middle, tapped to the leg side . Some turn there. The pitch has got slower and is taking spin
leans forward to push a full delivery to long-off
turns in from short of length, Yuvraj goes back to push it to covers
on the legs, turned to right of long leg for couple of runs
on a length, cutting in, pushed pas the lunging bowler and Rohit sets off for a single but Yuvraj says no as a fielder swoops on the ball
keeps low as it moves towards pads and he will pick up a single
another mistimed drive back to the bowler. The ball has begun to stop on the batsman on this sluggish track
Six over long-off. It was full pitched delivery and Yuvraj swung it high, Yousuf backpedalled, reached the ropes and the ball dipped behind him
cutting away from Yuvraj who pushes at it with an open-face of the bat, partly steered partly edged to the boundary
stretches well across to drive to sweeper cover
on the legs, the ball is really dirty and discolored, driven to long on
turns outside off stump, short of length and that length allows Rohit to punch it through point
on the pads, keeps low and turned to square leg
on the hips, tucked past square leg for a single
loopy delivery on the middle stump line, defended to the off side
on the off stump line, pushed to covers, they think about a single but decide against it as it went straight to the fielder. Yuvraj tells Rohit, "Start lekhe rakh" (Get a start and get ready)
shaping past the off stump, Yuvraj pushes inside the line and is beaten
leans forward to defend to mid-off
on the off stump line, angling away, dabbed to backward point
outside the off stump, steered to backward point
on a length, coming in towards middle and off, worked deftly to square leg
leg break from short of length and Rohit punches the new and whiter ball to long-off
this time a single down to long-off. Shabash Shahid bhai, shuts Akmal
full and outside off stump, Rohit mistimes his square drive to poitn
slower now and Rohit turns it to point
pretty close to being called a wide outside off
shout for lbw as the quick slider catches Rohit by surprise and hits him on the pad. Perhaps, just going down leg.
cutting away from Yuvraj who turns it to backward point.
walks down the track, tries to heave and mistimes it to deep midwicket for a single
just outside off, on a length, pushed to the on side
cutting towards off stump, punched through mid-off for a single
on the middle and leg, pushed towards mid-off
fuller, outside off and that length allows Yuvraj to drive inside out through extra cover for a boundary
on a length, outside off, pushed to covers
outside off stump, skids to Akmal as Rohit doesn't offer a stroke

cleans him up with a slider. It was slow through the air, landed on middle and leg and skidded towards leg. Rohit thought it would turn and was getting ready to cut to the off side and in the end, just managed to chop it on to his leg stump. Afridi points his finger to the skies and Rohit heads back to the hutch.
spins away after landing outside off stump, left alone
lunges forward to get a inside edge to the on side
almost caught by Afridi. It was a low dipping full toss and Yuvraj jabbed it well to the left of Afridi who lunged at it but couldn't reach it
walks down the track, Rao drags back the length, keeps it straight on the middle and Yuvraj pushes it back to the bowler
short , on the leg stump line and Yuvraj pulls to left of deep midwicket where Misbah stops near the ropes, he flicks it to Gul who fires the throw back to the 'keeper
short in length ,outside off, Dhoni gets across to push it through cover point for a single
lands outside leg stump on a length, comes towards leg stump, whipped off the pads past square leg
gets back and across to defend a length delivery on the middle and off stump line.
drifts towards middle and leg, turned to long leg for a single
leans forward to mistime a drive but will pick up a single to mid-on region
Slog swept over deep midwicket. He went down on his knee to dispose it over the boundary. Soaring six. It landed on the third tier
down leg side, misses a sweep but it's a wide
flighted full around off and driven crisply to long-off
leans forward to push to the off side
loopy turning delivery around off, squeezed off the outer edge to short third man
full almost yorker length on off, dug out to the off side
fab pull from Dhoni. It was banged in short at the body and he crashes it to the deep backward square leg  boundary
just outside off stump, punched off the back foot to covers
really full delivery, moved in a touch, jabbed to mid-off
length delivery coming in towards off and middle, pushed to point
punched straight to covers and ten overs remain in this innings. the over rate is pretty shoddy.
not all that short outside off and Yuvraj plays a delightful punchy drive over covers to left of sweeper cover.
short of length, angling away, dabbed to backward point
the slow bouncer, doesn't climb much and Dhoni waited before pulling it to deep backward square leg boundary
on a length, slanting away from Dhoni who punches it to covers
fuller, outside off stump, Dhoni opened the bat-face to slice it past the diving backward point fielder. skilful stroke
Brutal drive straight down the ground. It was full in length and he knifed it through the line in the air past the bowler.
starts off with a slower one full, Yuvraj waits to tap it past backward point for a single
on a length, coming in towards the off stump, dabbed to backward point
from round the stumps, coming in towards middle, pushed back to the bowler
low full toss and Dhoni drills it in the air past the startled bowler

trapped him in front with a full toss. Dhoni took couple of steps down the track and  tried to swing it across the line, missed, and was hit in front of middle and leg. On the back leg. Was it going down leg, though? Any way it doesn't matter. He is out.
driven to deep cover for a single
sharp bouncer and Raina sways away from the line.
full one, on the middle and leg, turned to midwicket where Yousuf stops and fires in a throw at non-striker's end
length delivery outside off, pushed to covers
Gul takes out Yuvraj. It landed on a length, on the middle, skidded in and Yuvraj was beside the line and was looking to punch-drive but the ball was tad fuller than he thought and it skidded through
leans forward to drive to mid-off
another wide from Wahab down the leg side
pushed to backward point
leans forward to work a full delivery past square leg
another wide down leg.
leans forward to drive to mid-off
shout for lbw but it  could have missed leg or could have hit leg stump. It cut in from the off stump and moved towards middle and leg. The virtual eye suggests it would have hit the stump.
on the pads, worked behind square leg
leans forward to push a length delivery to cover point
banged in short, pulled to deep square leg
short of length, outside off stump, tapped to cover point
bouncer and it went well above the batsman's head. wide signalled.
short of length, on the hips, tickled to fine leg
Raina heaves a length delivery over long-on. He just knifed through the line there.
low full toss, inside edges a drive to midwicket and rushes across and dives to make the crease in time

above waist-high full toss , around the head in fact, and down the leg side as well. Poor delivery. And this is second one well above the waist-high, beamer and he can't bowl any more. He has to go. He had bowled one such delivery in the 24 th over to Yousuf. He has bowled them at the two brothers! Obviously, it slipped off his hands. Now four guys confer to decide who will bowl. Malik, Afridi, Misbah and Younis Khan are the men. Aamir Sohail says he saw Younis Khan ask Malik to bowl and Malik pointed to his shoulder. And surprise it's going to be  Tanvir to bowl. Why would you waste two deliveries of your regular bowler?
on the middle and leg, turned to the leg side
short and outside off, cut past point
on a length, on the middle and off, pushed to the off side for a quick single
high full toss and Raina flat-bats it over long-on. Raina suggests it was above waist-high but the umpires reckon not.
full pitched on the leg stump line, driven to long-on for a single
down the leg side and another wide
turns a length delivery to wide third man and shouts immediately, "two two" and makes it back in time
on a length, on the middle and off, squeezed past point
slower one, Irfan backs outside leg and taps it to backward point
another full toss, just below waist and Irfan swings it to deep backward square leg boundary. It was on the leg stump.
leans forward to push it through covers for a single
slower one, dipping in front of the off stump, pushed to the off side for a single
just short of the blockhole, turned past square leg
full pitched outside off stump, driven hard to covers, Raina has run midway, turns back but the throw misses the stumps and he survives
short of length, flat batted to left of long-off
full and straight, swatted through midwicket
on a length, just outside off, punched to the off side
low full toss outside off, Irfan drives but makes contact with the toe end of the bat and spoons to Malik at covers. India are on 322 for 7
shout for lbw but there was an inside edge. Full and straight, Raina tried to get it to the leg side and edged it on to the pad
full in length, crashed to deep cover
Caught at deep square leg. Fullish, on the legs, swung straight to the fielder. Raina made 26 from 22
waist-high full toss, guided to wide third man for couple of runs
full in length, driven to long-on
length delivery outside off stump, swat pulled to midwicket. He mistimed that shot.
full toss on the middle and off, mistimes another drive through mid-off
Younis is bowling medium pace and bowls a nice yorker length delivery outside off, Chawla fails to connect and Akmal fails to collect cleanly
another one really full and outside off, Praveen tries to slice it away but misses.
another one at the base of the leg stump - this is good stuff from Younis- shoveled to midwicket

dot ball to finish the innings! Younis has done a fab job. On the blockhole on the middle, dug back to him. Younis has a big smile on his face. So does Malik who rushes to congratulate him. Praveen Kumar too laughs and Younis pats him on the back.

inn2.comm: pitched on a length, pushed to mid-off
short of a length, gets some away movement, Slman Butt flashes at it and is beaten
fullish on the pads and pushed square , another dot ball
on a length, just outside off, Butt crashes it towards cover, Suresh Raina misfields and a single results
Akmal gets off the mark straightaway, short ball and and a hint of away swing, Akmal guides it down to tird man
A slow, loopy bouncer from Praveen, and Butt fails to pick it. He's much too early on the pull and the ball sails harmlessly through to the wicketkeeper
let through to the keeper
Superb delivery that, 138kmph, on a length just outside off, Akmal attempts to drive away from his body and is beaten
that moved into the right-hander, clipped away towards midwicket
a similar delivery to the previous one, at 142.5 kmph, another dot ball
provides the width and Akmal launches into that, crashed through covers for the first boundary of the innings
pushed to point
short of a length, and moves away from the left-hander, Butt attempts a pull. mistimes it and they take two
short of a length and outside off, Butt slashes at it, catch is the cry but Ishant at the third man boundary can't hang on to a tough chance
Gone this time, a blinder from Rohit Sharma at cover point, Butt cuts it and Rohit dives to his left and takes a superb, low, one-handed catch

And another one, Pakistan are in deep trouble here. Angling away from the right-hander, tried to dab to third man but only manages to feather a simple catch to Dhoni. Ashoka de silva had no hesitation in sending Younis on his way
Half volley and swinging away, Yousuf drives it uppishly through cover point.
Retains the strike with a dab to third man
On a length, angling in, Yousuf taps it to the leg-side but no run results
Surprised him with a bouncer, that wasn't too short but kicked up, Yousuf does well to remove his bottom hand off the bat as he edges it. Doesn't carry though
defended to the leg side
Classy shot that. A perfectly-timed back foot square-drive for four
short of a length, Yousuf punches it to cover
Even that packed offside field can't stop that. Another lovely drive, this time slightly front of square.
Strays onto the pads, Akmal taps it down the ground, fielded at mid-on, no run
Fullish, some outswing, Akmal gets a thick outside edge and the ball runs away to third man for a single
on a length on middle, pushed to mid-on
this one cuts back in from a length, Yousuf shoulders arms to that one
That's the big one. Praveen Kumar is on fire here. pitches on a length on middle and shaped in, goes past his inside edge and raps him on the pads and that's the end of Yousuf
on a length, outside off, Misbah lets that go through to the keeper
good length on middle stump, Akmal drives it inside out, in the air but lands short of the mid-on fielder
cracking delivery that, in the corridor and Akmal is beaten
another excellent delivery. Almost a repeat of the previous one. Akmal is beaten again outsid off
Tries to steer it through leg but is beaten
shortish, angles in, Akmal smashes it behind square on the off, Yusuf Pathan does well to cut that off on the boundary
Ishant is maintaining a wonderful line here. Short delivery this time and defended off the back foot
on a length, darts inwards, takes a thick edge and rolls away sqaure on the leg side
Another edge and this sails through the vacant second slip region.
In the channel, Misbah get forward and defends that
short of a length, on off, Misbah fends it with soft hands and they scamper through for a quick single
strays on the leg side but Akmal doesn't capitalise on it. Hits his pads and a single results
Pushed towards off, no run
Six, Akmal makes use of Ishant's pace and bounce and upper cuts it over the third-man boundary. Paksitan need more of those
back foot punch to cover
jagged back sharply, Akmal wasn't comfortable dealing with that
pushed square on the off, dot ball
short and wide, Misbah attempts to cut but fails to connect.
better delivery this time, Misbah defends
exquisite straight drive from Akmal, slightly overpitched and Akmal pounced on it
another glorious drive, slightly to the off this time and easily beats the mid-on fielder
back of a length on the leg stump, Akmal tucks it behind square
Short and wide, Misbah mistimes it and no run comes off that ball
slow bouncer, and Misbah doesn't miss out this time, pulled away for four
Poor ball, whistling down leg, and Misbah helps it fine on the leg side for another boundary.
width offered, uppishly square driven, races away for four, splits backward point  and square point
slower ball, pushed to extra cover
back of a length, on the stumps, Misbah defends it confidently
good length, just outside off, Misbah leans into that and punches it to extra cover
wonderful drive from Misbah, slight width provided , Gambhir runs across from wide mid-off to try cut it off. Gets a hand to it but it still runs away for four
defended on the front foot, looking for a single but they decide against it
short of length, outside off stump, Akmal shapes to cut but the ball moves away further and he mistimes it to the off side
full and just outside off stump, mistimes a drive back to the bowler. Praveen has the ability to swing it back from that angle.
walks down the track and tries to heave a length delivery over midwicket and gets an inside edge on to the pad
slower one, on a length, well outside off stump, goes hard at the cut shot and sends it straight to covers
beaten outside off. On a length, lands outside off stump and straightens, Akmal wants to drive on the up and goes inside the line
shapes this one back in, from outside off stump, punched to covers and it's a maiden over
leans forward and drives on a bent back knee over mid-off and one bounce to the boundary. Eye-catching stroke that.
cuts to left of  backward point where Yuvraj makes a tumbling stop
slow delivery outside off stump, Misbah is made to wait and he pushes it to backward point
leans forward to dab a fuller length delivery to Yuvraj at backward point. Akmal shouts out No and Misbah, initially looking for a run, retreats
over pitched delivery around off stump and Misbah drives to right of mid-off where Gautam dives but can't stop the ball.
Akmal goes downtown. It's party time at Mirpur. He thrust his front foot out and hit a full-length delivery  through the line and over long-on.
short of length, wanted to flat bat it to wide mid-on but mistimes it
from round the stumps, a slower one arrives outside off, cut to cover point

Done in by a full toss from round the stumps. It swung in a touch and Akmal swatted it to mid-on and he is livid with himself.... Pakistan lose their fourth wicket.  Just when they were getting some momentum.
clips to the leg side for a single to get off the mark
in the zone outside off stump, a tad slower and is left alone
on a length, on the middle and is pushed to the leg side
coming in towards the off stump and defended to the off side
fuller, around off and middle, driven to left of Irfan who makes a tumbling stop and has a shy at the striker's end
off the short of length, just outside off, tapped towards gully
on the middle and leg, Malik shuffles across to get outside the line and glances it very. Nice deft touch. Good wrist work, too.
on the middle and on driven to Ishant at mid-on
outside off stump and edged to third man
well outside off stump and Dhoni gathers
straighter, fuller, just short of the blockhole and pushed down the track.
cuts in from just outside off stump, 87.1mph, and Malik covers his off stump, sees that there is no danger to it and shoulders arms
and again. A tad wider and easier decision to let it go through to Dhoni.
slower one, full and outside off, Malik lunges across to push it to covers.
slants it across Misbah who watches it sail into Dhoni's gloves
walks across the stumps, gets closer to the line of a full delivery further outside off and drives to left of mid-off
short of length, on the middle and leg line, tucked to fine leg and Praveen Kumar gets across to make the stop.
full length delivery outside off stump, drives straight to covers.
Dhoni has a packed off-side field. Just three men on the leg side and Irfan drifts to leg and middle, whipped past midwicket
walks across the stumps again, Irfan hurls it further outside off, sliced to wide third man
on the off stump line, nudged to the off side. The required rate is now 7 runs per over. The current rate is 5.81
Ishant takes out Misbah. Probing delivery outside off that straightened off a length and Misbah stabbed it to Dhoni. He was trying to run it down to third man but ...
kicks up from short of length but Afridi gets on the top of the bounce nicely to cut it to wide third man region

There is just one wide slip in place and this ball flew right between Dhoni and the slip fielder. It was full and outside off stump, Afridi flashed it to right of Dhoni who should have gone for it but just stood there and watched.
yorker on the off stump and Afridi brings his bat down in a hurry to keep it out to the off side.

another swing and a miss. Afridi is not wasting any time here. No settling down period; he is just going for it. It was a length delivery that straightened outside off and Afridi's bat went inside the line
really full delivery outside off stump, squeezed to cover point
another full pitched delivery from round the stumps, driven to extra cover
well outside off stump, pretty full, Malik stretches across and slices it to wide third man
short of length, coming in from that angle and Afridi uses it to lap it around to fine leg.
short of length, outside off stump, shaping in, dabbed to right of Sehwag at gully who makes a diving stop
moving towards middle stump, pushed wide of mid-on for a single
a touch short, outside off, cut to left of sweeper cover
leg break outside off stump and Malik tries to drive it through covers and gets a thick edge well to the right of the slip fielder
beaten on the cut. It was too full to play that shot and then was beaten by the extra bounce as well.
stretches across to push to covers where Rohit fails to make a clean stop and gives away a single
just outside off stump, Afridi went back , the ball skidded back in and he crouched to keep it out
conventional leg spin and Afridi plays it carefully to the off side
from round the stumps, lands it full on a length, just outside off stump and curves it back in, driven  back to Irfan
a tad slower, on the middle and off, pushed to Ishant, standing deep at mid-on, for a single
tries to heave a full delivery past the bowler but gets a thickish edge which takes the ball to wide third man
digs this one short and Malik hops to get on top of the bounce and tucks it to midwicket region for a single
slower in pace, short in length, drifting towards middle and leg, Afridi pulls it to deep backward square leg boundary.
yorker-length delivery lands on the boot of Afridi who tried to waft it to the on side. The angle was taking it down leg side
flighted delivery, slow through the air, outside off, driven uppishly through mid-on for a single
short and spinning away, cut to deep point
walks across the stumps, exposing the three sticks and wrists a loopy delivery on the off stump to backward square leg.
lovely deft late cut. It was the googly and he rocked back to cut it through backward point
lands just outside off, spins away, pushed to covers
similar delivery and Malik goes for the big slog sweep but fails to connect.
floated on the middle and Afridi gets a leading edge down the track
quicker, turned behind square leg
big appeal for lbw but the umpire says it went off the bat. It was the quick arm ball, Malik was late on the cut and even if it was pad first, he was struck outside the off stump
short delivery and Afridi pulls to deep midwicket boundary
leans across to paddle sweep a flighted delivery to fine-leg region
driven to wide long-on for a single
full and outside off, again driven to long-on region
turns away after landing on a length on the off stump, dabbed to backward point
slider outside off, a touch short and cut to deep point

stumped! Afridi telegraphed his intentions as he ran down the track too early and that allowed Piyush to bowl it quicker and outside off. Afridi had also moved outside leg and couldn't get bat on ball.
A googly first up for Tanvir, defended unconvincingly on the front foot
good length,sharp turn, batsman fails to connect the ball
outside off, cut away for a single
full delivery, on middle, Tanvir turns it to leg for a single
defended on the front foot
another dot ball, this is a good start from Yusuf
driven to long-on for a single
short ball on the stumps, keeps a bit low, Tanvir pushes it to mid-on for a single
good delivery from Chawla, shortish googly, defended off the back foot
on a length, appreciable turn, Tanvir gets on the front foot but misses it, balloons off the pads
turn in to Tanvir, tries to cut but that was too close to off
Tanvir finally manages a single
off-drive to cover for a single
pushed to mid-on for a single
And a huge six, Malik used his feet well, advanced down the track and hit cleanly over mid-on
short ball, turns in towards him, he turns it away down the leg side
back of a length, Tanvir get on the front foot and drives it through the off for a single
short ball, down leg side, lucky for Yusuf that it wasn't called a wide
anotehr dot ball, a stifled appeal for a catch as it whistles down leg side
good stuff from Chawla, no runs
Tanvir hasn't been very comfortable against Chawla, and that this time it goes uppishly off the leading edge, falls safely though
another single to the off side
Tanvir gets two through the covers
a big googly, Tanvir reads it but can't score off it

He's got him this time. Another googly, better direction than the previous one, Tanvir tries to hit it against the spin, he closes the face too early and the resulting leading edge hands Chawla a return catch
strays down the leg, paddled away for a couple
god length on off, defended on the front foot
similar delivery, manages to get a single this time
pitches it short this time, Malik cuts hard at it but should have score more than 1 off that
Umar Gul pushes that one back to the bowler
and again, good length just outside off, no run
short in length, goes back and turns it to deep midwicket
wide outside off, and he shoulders arms
too full this time, and Gul clobbers him over long-off for six
Gul lets that go as it kicks up from a length
turns it to midwicket for a single
pushes it towards point, a quick single is scampered
on middle, Malik turns it to midwicket
Stops on the batsman and he almost gives a return catch
another dot ball, defended more confidently this time

After two dot balls, Gul loses his patience. He tries to loft him over long-on but only manages to find Ishant Sharma in the deep. A smart catch from Ishant but he seems to have injured himself in the attempt.
pushed to cover, no run results
tosses that one up, turns and catches Ifthikar's outside edge, flies low towards slip but lands short
This has been a good spell from Chawla. Tosses up legspinner and beats the bat
flighted delivery, inside edge onto his pads
very wide this time, slashed through the off side
short and hit square on the off side
defends off the front foot
googly on a length, he was on the front foot and that struck him outside off, not out
slightly short of length outside off, cut past point and that's his fifty
turns past the forward prod
shorter and is pulled away for a single
goes right back to punch it to mid-off
fuller, closer to the off stump and driven past the diving Yuvraj Singh
leans forward to on drive to long-on
on a length, around that off stump, pushed back to the bowler
outside off stump, dabbed to backward point.
short of length, on the middle, pushed towards mid-on
well outside off, inside edges a square drive to the on side
on a length, straight on the stumps, punched to mid-on
cuts in a touch off short of length towards middle, worked to midwicket.
outside off stump, pushed to cover point. There is a slip and a gully in
on the middle and leg, stretches forward to defend

almost caught by Irfan Pathan at wide midwicket region. Very tough chance, though. Malik slog swept from outside off stump to the cowcorner and Irfan rushed across and dived but couldn't reach it as it dipped .
goes for the lofted shot over mid-off but edges it to right of mid-off where its held safely. And then they were one.
on a length, on the middle, squeezed to long leg region for couple of runs
outside the off stump, nudged to point
hit on the helmet. It was banged in short and Rao ducked but ducked straight into the ball
slightly slower one, back of length and Rao Iftikhar responds with a punchy drive off the back foot. Good comeback.
on the off stump line, pushed to covers
125.9 kmph  change of pace delivery and full in length, Rao Iftikhar picked it up early, leaned into his drive, and sent it soaring over wide mid-off region
leans forward to dab a full delivery to the off side
well flighted delivery, full, pushed to covers
lands outside off, sucking the batsman forward before spinning away

Dead plumb. Done by one that skidded on straight. It landed on a length around off and middle and caught him in front. He had expected it to turn and had stretched his front leg across and was surprised by the one that went on straight. India win by 140 runs.
